I make this recipe as berry crisp, making my own crumb topping and no pie crust. It has a been a huge hit with everyone I have served it to. I make it with cherries and blueberries. It is now a new summer favorite.

Rating: 4
This dessert outshined the main entree --lobster-- at our Summer lunch. Guests of all ages raved and doubled up. I had worried that the tapioca pearls I used (not quick cooking)would end up baked into little marbles amongst the cherries, but I made sure they were all well tucked in within the filling and they melted away in the syrup during the baking process. Be creative with the fruit. I used cherries, strawberries and blueberries. Anything goes. really. In fact substituting the disastrous crust in the Lattice Topped Apricot Tart (Bon Appetit May 2000) with this pie's crust recipe would yield any cook another show stopping sweet-and-tart fresh delight.

Rating: 4
I received rave- rave-rave reviews from this pie! The crust is fabulous, it looks terrific, and I made it with fresh picked blackberries and rasberries (there were no cherries..and no pitting to do!) Just the right balance of sweet to tart. Perfection.

