Rating: 4
My father-in-law recently handed me a container of fresh pie cherries from his tree. They were wonderful, but (I discovered after getting home) not enough for a whole cherry pie. What to do? This recipe was the perfect answer. I used a bag of frozen blackberries (organic). Our company was enraptured! Furthermore, I love making pies and experimenting with different crusts - and this one was a delight - effortlessly flaky and flavorful.

